Two ore bearing marble horizons: lower horizon >100 m thick, mostly mineralized in upper 60 m under the schist unit; upper horizon 60 m thick, mostly mineralized in the upper part under overthrust phyllite. Succession of mineral stages  by Leleu and others (1973): (1) volcanic- sedimentary pyrite+Pb-Zn-Ag; (2) skarn (+replacement) (Miocene) mt, po+ Pb-Zn-Ag; (3) karst Pb-Zn-Ag sulfide and oxide minerals.

Banded deformed sulfide ore from Olympas  is clearly intersected by the undeformed pegmatite vein on the photograph Fig. 4 from Kaloceropoulos (1989).
